The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Oudh Sugar Mills Ltd will raise Rs 100 crore from the international or the domestic market. The board has approved the proposal to raise the amount through foreign currency convertible bonds (FCCBs), GDRs, ADRs, equity shares or other securities, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. The company also plans to increase the capacity of its Hargaon distillery unit by 100 klpd (kilolitres per day). 

 Uttam Galva Steels Ltd has increased the prices of all its galvanised products in the domestic market by Rs 1,000 per tonne. The company said the price rise follows buoyant international market conditions. 

 Biocon Ltd has launched BIOMAb-EGFR, a drug to treat solid tumours of epithelial origin, such as head and neck cancers. The drug is engineered to target and block the epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) responsible for the proliferation of cancer cells. 

 Industrial Development Bank of India Ltd (IDBI) has been adjudged the best international bank in the categories of Corporate Customers and IT Team of the Year by the Institute for Development and Research in Banking Technology (IDRBT), in recognition of its customer centric IT initiatives.

 The board of Radha Madhav Corporation has approved the issue of 10,00,000 unsecured 10 per cent convertible debenture of Rs 100 each to Star Mauritius Ltd.

 Patel Engineerings consolidated net profit for 2005-06 was Rs 73.31 crore against Rs 41.55 crore a year ago. The company has declared a total dividend of 130 per cent for the year compared with 100 per cent a year ago.

 Indian Railways will use wireless communications technology of Nortel Wireless Network to upgrade the rail arteries in Uttar Pradesh.

 Active International has entered into a joint venture with AerenR Enterprises. The JV, Active International India, will bring corporate trade business models to India.

 Aztecsoft Ltd was ranked seventh among the top 20 Best IT Employers of the Year in India, according to a survey conducted by DataQuest Group and IDC India.

 IP Devel, a Romanian software firm has selected Compulinks Whizible SEM (Service Execution Management) suite. The Whizible suite is an enterprise-wide SEM solution.

